  • Method Details

    • customerCanBeDeleted

      public static boolean customerCanBeDeleted(Customer customer, javafx.collections.ObservableList<Appointment> allAppts)
      The customerCanBeDeleted method searches through the appointment list to see if any appointment's custID matches the selected customer's custID. If a match is found, the customer should not be deleted.
      Parameters:
      customer - The customer whose custID should be searched for.
      allAppts - An observable list of all appointments in the database.
      Returns:
      A boolean that is set to true if the customer is safe to delete and false if it is not.

    • getAllTypes

      public static javafx.collections.ObservableList<String> getAllTypes(javafx.collections.ObservableList<Appointment> appList)
      The getAllTypes method searches through the appointment list to find all of the appointment types in the database. It creates a new list of strings and adds each type provided it is not already in the list.
      Parameters:
      appList - An observable list of all appointments in the database.
      Returns:
      An observable list of String objects containing one instance of each appointment type.

    • getByMonth

      public static javafx.collections.ObservableList<Appointment> getByMonth(javafx.collections.ObservableList<Appointment> appList)
      The getByMonth method searches through the list of all appointments to find the ones that match the current month. LAMBDA: The lambda in this method sets up a filtered list from an observable list of all appointments in the database. This is filtered such that only appointments whose monthValue in the appointment's startDateTime matches the monthValue of the current month are included. This lambda enhances the application by simplifying the filtered list process into one line of code.
      Parameters:
      appList - An observable list of all appointments in the database.
      Returns:
      A filtered observable list of Appointment objects containing only those in the current month.

    • getByWeek

      public static javafx.collections.ObservableList<Appointment> getByWeek(javafx.collections.ObservableList<Appointment> appList)
      The getByWeek method searches through the list of all appointments to find the ones that match the current week. This list does not include past appointments. In the event that the current day is a Saturday, the next week's appointments will be included.
      Parameters:
      appList - An observable list of all appointments in the database.
      Returns:
      A filtered observable list of Appointment objects containing only those in the current week.

    • getApptsWithin15Min

      public static void getApptsWithin15Min(javafx.collections.ObservableList<Appointment> allAppts, User user)
      The getApptsWithin15Min method searches through the list of all appointments to see if any are within 15 minutes of the system's current time. If any are found, an alert is shown that tells the user what appointments they have in the next 15 minutes. If no appointments meet the criteria, an alert is shown that tells the user they have no upcoming appointments.
      Parameters:
      allAppts - An observable list of all appointments in the database.
      user - The current user.

    • appointmentOverlap

      public static Appointment appointmentOverlap(Appointment appointment, javafx.collections.ObservableList<Appointment> allAppts)
      The appointmentOverlap method searches through the list of all appointments to see if any appointments already occur during the appointment parameter. If any are found, it returns the conflicting appointment.
      Parameters:
      appointment - The appointment that might conflict with one already in the database.
      allAppts - An observable list of all appointments in the database.
      Returns:
      The appointment already in the database that conflicts with the appointment parameter.
